narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Economic and econometric analysis skills for labor economics
I think I learned a lot about the various aspects of labor economics, from job search to savings for retirement to education decisions
Key theoretical frameworks for labor economics.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: Wide range of topics covered during lectures Weaknesses: None

I think it struck a good balance of covering many topics and spending enough time with each one to appreciate it. I wouldn't have minded if less time was devoted to the theoretical econometric aspects of labor, although this may just be me.
I learned many different models in different topics and they are all interesting.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes. The course covers wide range of topics in labor economics.
Yes, to those interested in the economics of workers I think this semester was very good, although the workload is nontrivial
Yes. The topics are interesting, and professor is very nice.
Yes, I would recommend. It provides useful knowledge and insights for those who are interested in labor economics.
